do is a Java keyword.It starts a do-while looping block. The do-while loop is functionally similar to the while loop, except the condition is evaluated after the statements executeSyntax:do {
    //statements;
} while (condition);For example:do {
    i++;
} while ( i < maxLoopIter );See also:Java Programming/Statements
